The fourth Mid-Year Co-ordination Meeting preceded by the 41st Ordinary session Executive Council that centred on Nutrition and Food Security, saw the creation and launch of a number of programmes like that focusing on different developmental agendas like the Inter-Regional Knowledge Exchange on Early Warning and Conflict Prevention, Education Plus Initiative, second edition of the Young Africans Writing Contest and The Policy Booklet on the ‘Migration Policy Framework for Africa. The current context, structured by numerous crises, prompts us to review our toolbox with a view to improving the economic and political governance of the continent in order to better assert our geopolitical personality on the international scene. AU Commission Chairperson, Moussa Faki Mahamat, says the situation Africa faces requires leaders to review their ‘toolboxes’. “The current context, structured by numerous crises, prompts us to review our toolbox with a view to improving the economic and political governance of the Continent in order to better assert our geopolitical personality on the international scene,” Faki Mahamat said. -- Arthur Davies Sikopo/ Channel Africa--